{
  "stem": "33.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I didn't know the rest of my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "My parents were-- my mother was the youngest child in her family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And my father was in the younger generation in his family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] So two of my grandparents on my mother's side and my grandfather on my father's side died before I was born, so I never knew them.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "[SIGHS] About a week before we left, we were-- we were to be the last people to be evacuated since we were the last ones, among the last ones to get into the ghetto area.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Something happened to my mother that decided her fate at an early stage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "In this one kitchen where all these women tried to cook dinner at night, or make something, somebody by accident dropped a tea kettle with boiling water and my mother was standing nearby.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And she burned one foot pretty badly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Our own family physician was also in the ghetto, and he did take care of her.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "But a week later, when we were evacuated, she was still wearing slippers on that foot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "It was healing nicely, but it wasn't completely healed yet.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "Since the small hospital that was in the ghetto was also evacuated in the same time we were, my father was very happy because he was able to arrange for my mother to travel with hospital patients and also doctors and their families, I think, that were in those two hospital cars, where there were only 30 people to the same size of cattle car that the rest of us were maybe 150 too.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "So my mother would be able to sit down and put her foot up and be a little more comfortable since her foot wasn't still-- you know, her burn wasn't completely healed.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
